Task_Description:
Hi Maddie. 
Thank you for the video. That is looking really good. A few points come to mind. 
 
1. Really like the 'adding an LMS course in the CRM'. That will mean that i can create lots of courses and then manually allocate them to the contractors portal page (NB: This may mean that we rename this page to 'Induction and Learning Centre' and keep the menu item there when they are fully inducted for the future training). 
 
2. Can the text on each induction page be bigger? 
 
3. I discussed with Hassan to have a format for each page, with a next button at the bottom. I didn't see a text page to confirm this. 
 
4. At the end of each Quiz can you say something like they 'You have been successful with Module 1. Please proceed to the next Module" 
 
5. What happens if they choose an incorrect answer? 
 
6. So in your video, does that mean they only have to do the quiz to complete the module (all information pages I see become ticked). Don't they have to read each page, with a time counter on each to slow them down to make sure they spend time reading it as I discussed with Hassan? 
 
7. At the end of the course do we have a statement that says - 
"You have successfully completed the online induction. Could you now NOW please go back into the Furlong Painting Portal and submit the relevant documents." 
And have a button to take them back to a refreshed portal page that now shows the documents menu. 
 
8. By default, after they have successful finished the course, I would like the course to disappear from their Induction and Learning Page won't it (unless i re-enroll them in the course again) 
 
9. Can the certificate of completion be a little acknowledgement and not a big certificate please? Just needs to have: 
- Furlong Logo 
- name of contractor 
- name of course 
- date completed 
 
10. Have you developed the same for the sub contractor course? 
 
11. Is there a capacity on each page to have a pop up with a few language translation options? 
 
12. After this does the CRM record then tick 'Course completed' and save the dates in their record. 
 
13. Can we take away the course expiry date altogether please. 
 
14. Can they save the draft if left unfinished and go back to it? 
 
15. How would they go back to the portal page when done to upload documents?
